# Design System Rules

## Reference
Always refer to `specs/design-system.md` for the complete design specification.

## Core Principles
1. **Dark Theme First** - Use dark backgrounds (`bg-primary`, `bg-secondary`, `surface`)
2. **Speed Optimized** - All interactive elements must meet touch target minimums
3. **Neon Sports Aesthetic** - Use glows and vibrant accent colors

## Color Usage
- **Primary (#00F5A0)**: Success states, points scored, primary actions
- **Accent (#FF6B35)**: Warnings, fouls, turnovers, away team
- **Highlight (#00D4FF)**: Links, info states, assists

## Touch Targets (MANDATORY)
- Minimum interactive element size: `48px` (`--tap-target-min`)
- Primary action buttons: `64px` (`--tap-target-lg`)
- Player selection tiles: `80px` (`--tap-target-xl`)

## Typography
- Display/Scores: `font-display` (Bebas Neue)
- Headings: `font-heading` (Space Grotesk)
- Body text: `font-body` (Inter)

## Component Patterns

### Buttons
```tsx
// Primary button
className="min-h-[var(--tap-target-lg)] px-6 bg-primary text-text-inverse font-heading font-semibold rounded-[var(--radius-md)] hover:shadow-[var(--glow-primary)] active:scale-[0.98] transition-all duration-[var(--duration-fast)]"

// Ghost button
className="min-h-[var(--tap-target-md)] px-4 bg-transparent border border-border text-text-primary rounded-[var(--radius-md)] hover:bg-bg-hover transition-colors duration-[var(--duration-fast)]"
```

### Cards
```tsx
className="bg-surface border border-border rounded-[var(--radius-lg)] p-4 shadow-[var(--shadow-md)]"
```

### Inputs
```tsx
className="h-[var(--tap-target-md)] px-4 bg-bg-tertiary border border-border rounded-[var(--radius-md)] text-text-primary placeholder:text-text-muted focus:border-border-focus focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary-glow"
```

## Animation Guidelines
- Use `--duration-fast` (100ms) for hover states
- Use `--duration-instant` (50ms) for button presses
- Always respect `prefers-reduced-motion`
- Use `animate-stat-confirm` for stat entry feedback
- Use `animate-score-pulse` for score updates

